Managing local users and group 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* To create a user and group we have two command 

1) useradd u1 ==> to add user 1 
whereas : 
         U1 means user1 
         
2) adduser u2  = to add user 2 

Note =  To add a second user we did not create directly useradd U2 we have to make by command adduser u2
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* To set a password for the respective user 

3) passwd u1 ==> to create a password 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* To fetch or see the complete user information 

4) vi /etc passwd ==> This command will show all existing and new user details. 4
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* To fetch or to see user password information 

5) vi /etc/shadow ==> This command will show all existing and new users password details 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* To create a group 

6) ==> groupadd G1 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* To fetch or see the complete information about the group  (secondary group) 

7) ===> vi /etc/group
